Rainfall in different parts of Mexico could be heavy, with a considerable risk of flooding.
According to weather.com, 75 to 150 mm of rain totals are expected from Baja California to northwestern Sonora, with the possibility of up to 250 mm.
After that, Rosa will head northward crossing Mexico as a tropical storm, before reaching the Arizona border early Tuesday morning as a tropical depression, and finally crossing Arizona and reaching southern Utah late Tuesday night.
"The main risk we expect from the Rosa or what's left of it is very heavy rainfall in Baja California, northwestern Sonora and the desert of the southwestern United States", according to the National Hurricane Center.
