The one-hour course includes a series of interactive tasks.
In one section is a picture of a dorm room, where students have to click on coffee cups, curtains, beds and books to receive information about the effects of caffeine and light, about how it affects sports performance on sleep deprivation, and about the importance of maintaining a bedtime routine.
