Year after year, however, the number of people living with HIV and AIDS in China has increased by 100,000.
Sexual transmission of HIV is a serious problem for the LGBT community in China.
Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but discrimination against LGBT people is common.
Given the country's conservative values, studies estimate that between 70 and 90 percent of men who engage in homosexual relationships will end up marrying a woman.
Many disease transmissions are due to the lack of proper precautions in sexual relations.
Since 2003, the Chinese government has pledged universal access to HIV medication as part of an effort to address the problem.
