Review of Johnny English Strikes Again: a parody of the limited spy by Rowan Atkinson
It's a tradition to look for Brexit references in any new film with a British focus, and this remake of the Johnny English parody action-comedy franchise, which was born in 2003 with Johnny English and reappeared in 2011 with Johnny English Reborn, is no exception.
This humorous self-satire about how despicable we are will be a new opportunity for the country's export?
