Evidently, it's the stupid secret agent who, despite his rare claims of glamorous glamour, has a bit of Clouseau, a bit of Mr. Bean and a touch of this guy who brings a single note to the theme of Chariots of Fire at the opening ceremony of the London 2012 Olympic Games.
Originally, it was based on the international and mysterious traveller Atkinson who represented the now forgotten television advertisements for Barclaycard, where he was spreading chaos everywhere.
There are one or two good moments in this last JE trip.
