You can see Atkinson's gift for physical comedy, but the humor seems pretty fluid and strangely superfluous, especially since "serious" film brands like 007 and Mission Impossible now include comedy as an ingredient.
The humor seems to be aimed at children rather than adults, and, to me, Johnny English's absurd adventures are not as witty or focused as the silent gags of Atkinson's Mr. Bean character.
The recurringly topical premise now is that Britain is in serious trouble.
A hacker has infiltrated the British super secret web spy network and revealed the identities of all British agents on the ground, to the consternation of the service agent, a pitifully small role for Kevin Eldon.
