English and Bough begin their odyssey of ridiculous antics: disguised as waiters, they set a French fast food restaurant on fire, cause chaos by smuggling contraband aboard Volta's luxury yacht, and English causes a major confusion by trying to use a virtual reality helmet to familiarize himself with the interior of Volta's house.
All the stops are certainly taken from this last sequence, but with all the simplicity and noise it presents, everything together seems like a children's program.
Just like normal things.
As with other Johnny English films, it has been no help to wonder if the film industry has given Rowan Atkinson a role that does justice to her talent.
