He later ran towards the line of fire and, with "the utmost courage" he advanced the line before throwing himself on a cannon with one hand and leaving three members of the detachment stunned.
The lieutenant colonel was shot by a German sniper on October 4, 1918, just a month before the war ended.
Michael Vann (72) said that his grandfather's actions were a feat he could never match, which produces a sense of humility.
He and his brother, Dr. James Vann, also left a crown after the parade, conducted by the Brentwood Imperial Youth Band.
