The German Navy's new frigate was supposed to be completed in 2014 to replace the Cold War era warships, but won't be ready until at least next year due to faulty systems and rising costs, according to local media.
The completion of the "Rheinland-Pfalz", the lead ship of the new Baden-Württemberg-class frigates, has been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit, citing a military spokesman.
The ship was supposed to have joined the Navy in 2014, but problems following construction have put an end to this ambitious project.
The four Baden-Württemberg-class ships that the Navy commissioned in 2007 will replace the old Bremen-class frigates.
