But there are still many things we don't know about bats, so the work we do here and on other properties will help us better understand what they need to grow".
He points out the importance of checking for bats before doing maintenance tasks on properties, as it may be that the possible involuntary destruction of a single maternity nest kills more than 400 females and young, which could lead to the disappearance of an entire local population.
Bats are protected and it is illegal to kill them, attack them, harass them, and destroy their nests.
Elisabeth Ferrell, an official with the Scottish Bat Conservation Foundation, has encouraged people to step forward to help.
He said: "We still have a lot to learn about bats and, in the case of some of our own species, we don't have enough data on their population".
